name: Clinkers cake
description: Two delicious layers of vanilla cake and a Clinkers-studded cheesecake centre are covered in a fluffy pink buttercream and decorated with even more Clinkers.

name: Chocolate croissant
description: This easy chocolate croissant recipe is a simplified version that uses puff pastry to make this delicious pastry in less than 30 minutes! They make a great breakfast treat and they are perfect for Sunday brunch!

name: Baguettes
description: At some point in every amateur bread baker’s life comes the desire to tackle the baguette, and for good reason: Great baguettes are hard to come by outside of France.

name: Stawberry macarons
description: Macarons are known for being deliciously delicate sandwich cookies that come in various colors and flavors, but they also have a notorious reputation for being tricky to create at home.

name: Espresso martini cake
description: Chocolate sponges are drizzled with boozy coffee syrup then layered up with an indulgent espresso mascarpone icing. This showstopper is luscious and rich.

name: Tuna Croissont Sandwich
description: Take a delicious classic to the next level with a tender, flaky croissant instead of plain white or wheat bread.

name: Rustic Bread
description: There's nothing better than homemade bread, fresh out of the oven.

name: French macaron
description: These French macarons make a very special treat to give your friends and family. They also look pretty on a plate for guests to indulge in when they come over.

name: Croissant toast
description: Surprise someone special with this irresistible French toast made with croissants, thickened cream and strawberries. Drizzle with maple syrup for the ultimate finish.

name: Berry mille-feuille
description: Delicate and sweet Danish pastries with various fillings.

name: Matcha-Almond
description: Scones filled with fresh raspberries and a hint of almonds.

name: Ciabatta bread
description: The “French stick” usually comes to mind when we think of French bread. It is a long, thin, crusty loaf typically called a “baguette,” which directly translates into “a stick.”

name: Chocolate macarons
description: The ganache filling and the macarons are best made a day in advance and kept in the fridge in an airtight container.

name: Sourdough bread
description: A rich, nutty flavour – with a punchy, sour tang – enhanced by a 7-seed mix and pumpkin seeds. This long fermented, yeast free loaf is a wholesome source of good fats and omegas.

name: Carrot Cake
description: Moist and spiced carrot cake with cream cheese frosting.

name: Korean Fat-caron
description: We’ve created a variety of flavor combinations for our French dessert, which is stuffed with luscious buttercream.

name: Pestashio Custardy
description: When the geometry and the hygrometry align like this, the buttery sheets can be pleated and pinched, folded and braided, rolled and dyed.

name: Chocolate Chip Banana Bread
des,cription: Freshly baked Banana bread is waiting for you. It’s worth the wait! ,so happy to have chocolate chips in this loaf of bread.

name: Chantilly Cake
description: A truly beautiful combination of smooth chantilly frosting layered between light and moist vanilla cake.

name: Ddungcaron
description: One of the reasons for the popularity of Fatcarons is in their unique designs.

name: Rainbow croissants
description: A chocolate cake with rainbow croissants sits on a table next to a cake with colorful candy.

name: Pastel macrons
description: Freshly baked pastel macrons, perfect for breakfast.
